lead_paragraph: Prof. ALEXANDER D. BACHE, the efficient Superintendent of the U. S. Coast Survey, has just presented to the Secretary of the Treasury a statement of the topography of the principal harbors on the Pacific Coast. The observations were made in connection with the Coast Survey, at Trinidad, Humboldt and San Diego Bays, by Lieutenant Commanding James Alden, U. S. N.; assistant R. D. Cutts, and sub-assistant A. M. Harrison.
